               <msContents>
                  <summary>Private account of parcels of land, arranged by cultivator, probably listing rents; the crops are wheat, barley, flax, and hay; these are the accounts of a large landowner</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">The Princeton piece is the upper part; together with the Columbia piece the text is almost complete</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; the text continues on the back across the fibers</note>
                     <note type="general">35 lines of writing all together; the Columbia piece includes part of line 11, lines 12-19 and 31-35; the hand is large, with many flourishes, and should belong to the 2nd half of the century</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
